We record a preregistered batch of 50 three-dimensional facial landmark sets and bind them to modular arithmetic witnesses via a signed receipt chain. Let \Delta(q)=q\prod_{n\ge 1}(1-q^n)^{24}=\sum_{n\ge 1}	au(n)q^n. Faces are interpreted as morphic embeddings admitted to a modular basin; receipts carry SHA-256 anchors and optional OP\_RETURN pointers.\
